---
import SiteLayout from "../components/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Astropress WordPress Migration"
  description="Astropress supports WordPress migration as a staged import workflow with typed artifacts, reports, and operator review."
  heading="WordPress migration is supported as a staged workflow, not a fake one-click promise."
  currentPath="/wordpress"
>
  <section class="panel-grid">
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>What the importer does today</h2>
      <p>
        It inspects WordPress exports, builds an inventory and import plan, stages content, media, comments, users,
        taxonomies, and redirects as artifacts, and records remediation candidates for anything that needs manual
        review.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="panel">
      <h2>What it does not claim</h2>
      <p>
        Astropress does not present the current importer as a fully automatic hosted migration into every runtime. If a
        source site has shortcode or page-builder debt, the artifacts and reports should make that debt explicit.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="panel">
    <h2>CLI workflow</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><code>astropress import wordpress --source export.xml</code></li>
      <li>Review the generated inventory, plan, report, and remediation artifacts.</li>
      <li>Optionally add <code>--artifact-dir</code>, <code>--download-media</code>, <code>--apply-local</code>, or <code>--resume</code>.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
